                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/>ἐνθάδε κῖτε <g ref="#staurogram">𐆠</g>
                        <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name>Ἀγάθων</name></persName> πιστὸς
                        <lb n="3"/>ζήσας ἔτη <num value="7">ζ</num> <expan><abbr>μ</abbr><ex>ῆ</ex><hi rend="ligature"><abbr>νας</abbr></hi></expan>
                        <lb n="4"/><num value="7">ζ</num> ἀνεπαύσατο
                    <lb n="5"/><roleName type="supracivic" subtype="consul"><expan><abbr>ὑ<hi rend="ligature">πατ</hi></abbr><ex>ίᾳ</ex></expan></roleName> <persName type="attested"><name>Ὀνωρίου</name></persName> τὸ <num value="8">η</num>
                        <lb n="6"/><choice><orig>κὲ</orig><reg>καὶ</reg></choice> <persName type="attested"><name>Θεοδοσίου</name></persName> τὸ <num value="3">γ</num> <expan><abbr>Σε
                    <lb n="7" break="no"/>β</abbr><ex>αστῶν</ex></expan>  <expan><abbr>Α<am>α</am>υ<am>ὐ</am>γ<am>γ</am></abbr><ex>ούστων δυοῖν</ex></expan> τῇ πρὸ <num value="5"><choice><sic>γ</sic><corr>ε</corr></choice></num> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g>
                        <lb n="8"/>εἰδῶν Ὀκτωβρίων
                        <lb n="9"/>ἡμέρᾳ Σελήνης <g ref="#staurogram">𐆠</g>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text of IG 14.0444</note></app></listApp>
                <app loc="7"><note>Ferrua 1982 and 1989: corrects Γ to Ε</note></app>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Ferrua notes that the date must be corrected, if it is to align with the consulship year of 409. Note the day recorded as day of the moon; and note the combined use of Greek and Latin abbreviations for Augustus, the latter in Greek letters.
                    <!--enthade keitai; chi-rho symbol; Agathon; Age in years and months; cos. date of death, together with day and month; Note that the day is specified as that of Selene. F corrects the date from 409 to 411. Photograph from Lorenzo Campagna--></p>
            </div>
